All of this complex front end framework stuff I really don&#x27;t see that it is necessary. You can write basically the most important part of the framework into a very small coffeescript file.<p><a href="https://gist.github.com/Kequc/11083050" rel="nofollow">https://gist.github.com/Kequc/11083050</a><p>Then your class:<p><pre><code>  class MyApp.Cat

    constructor: (data) ->

      @element = $(&#x27;<div class=&quot;cat&quot;></div>&#x27;)

      @update = new MyApp.Update @,
        name: (v) =>
          @element.text v
        color: (v) =>
          @element.css backgroundColor: v

      @update.all data

  new MyApp.Cat
    name: &quot;Gary&quot;
    color: &quot;#FF00FF&quot;</code></pre>
